abh\">section h\u003C/span>\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divh--diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"ah-l1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Τ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abi\">section i\u003C/span>\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"divi--diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"ai-l1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>sign, uninterpreted\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003657_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; Marconi 1926, fig.27\" src=\"ISic003657_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003657.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; Marconi 1926, fig.27\" src=\"ISic003657-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based upon the apograph in Marconi 1926; Marconi presents several of the letters 'reversed', but given that the orientation of a mason's mark need not follow the final orientation of the stone, this does not seem significant\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"e.1\">e.1: \u003Cspan>The symbol has the form of an hourglass\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"i.1\">i.1: \u003Cspan>The symbol has the form of an incomplete (upper left) and open (at the waist) hourglass\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u0